liche Auseinandersetzung zu formulieren. Zu den Autorinnen und Autoren der hier diskutierten Texte gehören u.a. Saul Ascher, Fritz Bernstein, Nathan Birnbaum, Isaac Breuer, Constantin Brunner, Christian Konrad Wilhelm von Dohm, Norbert Elias, Eduard Fuchs, Emma Goldman, Julius Goldstein, David Kaufmann, Bernard Lazare, Moritz Lazarus, Leo Trotzki, Mark Vishniak und Arnold Zweig.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aAntisemitismxHistory. 4a19. Jahrhundert. 4a19th century. 4aAnti-Semitism. 4aAntisemitismus. 4aTheoriebildung. 4atheory formation. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh1 aHahn, Hans-Joachim, eeditor.1 aKistenmacher, Olaf, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2014z9783110370225oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831103957160 cprintz978311033905540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110339062423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110339062.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014